    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-04-27T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-04-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="737"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d737">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/11737.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">Lorillard</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Buenos Aires</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-04-27">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 27, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Argentine Government has received information that Huerta will accept mediation.
                    Minister for Foreign Affairs tells me offer of mediation on the part of this
                    Government was made at the suggestion of Naón, who proposed it to his Brazilian
                    and Chilean colleagues. He has been given full powers to act as he deems best in
                    the premises.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lorillard</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
